REGISTRY AUTHORITATIVE (P5.1): When SKILL.md and registry templates (`manifest.yaml` + `.j2`) conflict, registry wins. This template is the canonical `emit-regulation` phase definition.
PUBLIC VISIBILITY: `visibility: public` — no hidden runtime regulation controls (P3, P4).
NO FABRICATION: Only threats with quoted span evidence are regulated. Only regressions with concrete `pattern` (regex against span target / signal value) are proposed. Only defense layers with actual `cns.guard.*` / `cns.regulation` span emission are counted as firing.
NO SYNTHETIC DATA: `evidence_snippet` must be verifiable by inspecting the running system's CNS telemetry at the cited timestamp. `span_target`, `timestamp`, `signal_value` must reference actual emitted spans. `block_reason` must reference concrete evidence (severity + defense-layer silence).
CONVERGENCE INDEPENDENT: Convergence-check is a separate phase; this emit-regulation phase does not compute metric (that is `convergence-check.j2` responsibility). This maintains pipeline decomposition (P5 minimalism — each phase answers one 5W1H dimension clearly).
